, "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "GnRH", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9971715211868286, "span": {"begin": 426, "end": 430}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5351"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "luteinizing hormone", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9875712394714355, "span": {"begin": 484, "end": 503}}], "text": "The release of gonadotrophin-releasing hormone (GnRH) stimulate the secretion of &nbsp;luteinising hormone (LH) (Fields et al., 2009). GnRH causes the pituitary gland to secrete LH. Gonadotropin releasing hormone (GnRH) is the key regulator of the secretion of luteinising hormone (Marques et al., 2018; Bowen et al., 1998; Tsutsumi and Webster, 2009). Metastin or kisspeptin in the control of gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) release and then it causes for pulsatile release of luteinizing hormone(Ohkura et al., 2009).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:55:55 +0000 2026"}